reviews.text: Good food and coffee
Amazing place, good in taste.

All I can say is really, really, really good for the money. Service is a bit crappy, but the food is excellent value for money. At first I thought the menu was in US dollars lol. Pizza for 30 hkd and a clam pasta for under 30 hkd what's not to like? Highly recommended and popular place to eat for obvious reasons, just expect poor service but good value food.
Food quality has gotten worse, Staff unfriendly and price has gone up. The environment was messy dirty and messy. Not recommend to go,
It so very inexpensive which you can enjoy the amazing food. I think the quality of food is quite good, not very good, not very bad.

reviews.text: Not a bad after all. a few decent chinese restaurants you can find inside the mall with affordable rates.
There is a park n shop, a couple of 7-11's, a fortress electronic store, Mcdonalds and a watsons here. There are plenty of other shops here too. You don't need to travel far to get what you need.

A neighbourhood mall with lots of variety to choose from. Obviously, it has the ubiquitous fashion chains like baleno, bossini. Restaurants are plenty although I struggle to find my favourite HK style restaurant, although you see the usual MX & Cafe de Coral. Do try the Shanghainese restaurant, not bad at all.

To add to the above, there is a Broadway cinema.

Interesting find is you can even see a few bakeries, not something that common these days in malls.
Rents keep going up so shops keep closing. New shops after a quick buck and you can't count on them being there for long.
The biggest mall in Tin Shui Wai. Good selection of shops, restaurants and cinema. Not bad and ample of car park space.
